a_id: ### The lines below are comments and examples. Please remove before adding your asset and vulnerability data.
### Use one line for each vulnerability, and repeat the asset information as required.
### "a_id" is Phoenix Security's asset ID. If you use this ID none of the other asset columns are required and they will be ignored.
### "v_details" is a custom JSON text with attributes for the vuln. It will not be processed in any specific way - it will be displayed in vulns details area.
### Info about each column. See note about "a_id" above.
a_resource_type: Fully qualified repo name (required for Repository; optional for others)
at_build: JAR file, ZIP file, Snyk project,... (required for Code)

a_id: ### "a_tags" & "v_tags" are optional - JSON array of strings or objects (see examples)
